{
  "stem": "27340.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But the rest of the family all perished or were suffering from tremendous atrocities.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I didn't really see much point in maintaining this adherence.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- to Judaism, who knows what was the future going to bring?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And while I didn't become an agnostic, I didn't have much opportunity in Walsall anyway to retain Judaism per se.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so I let that whole concept of Judaism slip consciously until we went to this camp.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This camp happened to have been run by an organization, the halutz organization, called Habonim.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was at that camp, at which we were only for one week, we met people of our age group, boys and girls.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Apart from the fact that I fell in love with one of the girls there, the boys and all the other people impressed me immensely.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They seemed to have a specific purpose.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were Zionistically oriented.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They wanted to live on the kibbutz, and they wanted to deal with agriculture.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I became smitten, if I can call it that, by the bug.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The Habonim was organized extremely well throughout the country, and wherever there were Jewish communities, there were also Habonim groups.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so I was invited to the Habonim group in London, and there were about 18 of them, senior groups, two-- two Habonim groups in Birmingham.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It flattered my ego.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But at the same time, I was beginning to see some sort of contact with other people, many of whom had a similar sort of background to my own.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There were, perhaps, in this Habonim movement, 50% of the members were refugees.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The others were British born and obviously felt the pain of the people in a similar way as we did, perhaps not as directly as we did.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
